# Architecture Decisions — {{PROJECT_NAME}}

> The canonical project ledger of locked architectural and strategic calls. One file per project, root-level, version-controlled.
> AI agents: read this before proposing changes. Never re-open a settled question without writing a *new* numbered entry that explicitly supersedes the old one.

## What goes here (and what doesn't)

In: non-obvious calls with cross-cutting impact, evidence-backed enough to defend for ≥90 days, with a reversal trigger that is decidable from observable facts.

Out: changelog entries (what was *built* — that's git history), one-PR-and-done decisions (commit messages handle those), preferences enforceable by linter/typecheck (rules handle those), temporary calls (code comments handle those).

Background discipline + entry anatomy + reversal/re-verify mechanics: see [KB-04 §2](../../../knowledge-base/KB-04-DECISION-ENGINEERING.md#2-pillar-1--decision-lock-discipline-decisionsmd).

---

## Pick your tier

This template carries all three maturity tiers from KB-04 §8. Use the lightest one that fits — graduate when the warning signs at the bottom fire.

- **Tier 1 — Starter.** Solo developer, side project, <10 cross-cutting decisions total. One-line entries.
- **Tier 2 — Intermediate.** Multi-week project, multiple consequential decisions, single-pass synthesis. Full entry structure with reversal triggers and re-verification cadence.
- **Tier 3 — Advanced.** Multi-orchestrator, multi-month, strategic stakes. Full discipline: TL;DR + Master Synthesis 400w + Full Body + Reversal + Re-verify + Cross-DECISIONS Reconciliation.

Delete the tiers you don't use. Keep the one you do, then add entries below it.

---

## Tier 1 — Starter format

Single-line entries. Date + decision + one-sentence reason. Cap at ~15-20 entries before graduating to Tier 2.

### Active Decisions

- **{{DATE_1}}** — {{DECISION_1}}
  <!-- example: "2026-03-15 — Named exports only, no defaults. Reason: barrel exports and tree-shaking work better." -->

- **{{DATE_2}}** — {{DECISION_2}}
  <!-- example: "2026-03-20 — Zod schemas colocated with route handlers, not in shared schemas/. Reason: easier to find and change together." -->

- **{{DATE_3}}** — {{DECISION_3}}
  <!-- example: "2026-03-22 — Tests colocated next to source files, not in __tests__/. Reason: easier to find, less directory switching." -->

Graduation signal: a decision starts getting re-debated despite being in the ledger. Move to Tier 2.

