## Tier 2 — Intermediate format

Full entry structure per decision, but synthesis remains single-pass (no Layer 2 protocols). Apply the [8-gate framework](../../../knowledge-base/KB-04-DECISION-ENGINEERING.md#31-layer-1--the-8-gate-input-filter) to any research dossier that backs a Tier 2 entry.

### Implementation #{{N}} — {{TITLE}} ({{DATE}})

**Decision** — {{CHOSEN_PATH_AND_KEY_TRADEOFFS}}
<!-- example: "Adopt next-intl v4 over react-intl. Trade lower bundle size + native App Router support for less mature plugin ecosystem." -->

**Rationale** — {{WHY_THIS_PATH_VS_ALTERNATIVES}}
<!-- example: "react-intl required wrapper hacks for server components; next-intl ships first-class App Router support. Bundle delta ~12KB gz. Plugin ecosystem gap mitigated by 4 existing in-house ICU helpers." -->

**Reversal triggers** — {{2_TO_4_DECIDABLE_TRIGGERS_WITH_ALTERNATIVE_PATHS}}
<!-- example: "(1) next-intl drops App Router support → migrate to FormatJS direct. (2) Bundle parity disappears (>20KB delta) → reassess. (3) Project needs ICU MessageFormat features next-intl lacks → fork or migrate." -->

**Re-verify** — {{CADENCE}} via {{MONITORING_CHANNEL}}
<!-- example: "Quarterly: next-intl release notes + GitHub issue tracker for App Router status. Annual: full library re-evaluation." -->

**Cross-references** — {{LINKED_ENTRIES_OR_RULES}}
<!-- example: "Preserves Implementation #4 (locale URL structure). Touches `.claude/rules/cms-i18n.md`." -->

Graduation signal: a decision requires >4 research dossiers, OR your single-pass synthesis missed a cross-dossier contradiction that downstream work surfaced. Move to Tier 3.

