## Tier 3 — Advanced format

Full discipline. Layer 1 (8 gates) per dossier, Layer 2 (8 analytical protocols) at synthesis time, Layer 3 (forward construction) for the locked entry. Universal Blocks A/B/C in every dossier. See [KB-04 §3](../../../knowledge-base/KB-04-DECISION-ENGINEERING.md#3-pillar-2--the-3-layer-research-architecture) for the architecture.

The TL;DR + Master Synthesis are the canonical Layer 2 Protocol 8 + Protocol 6 outputs, verbatim. Don't re-derive them — paste them in.

### Implementation #{{N}} — {{TITLE}} ({{DATE}})

#### TL;DR (Protocol 8 — smart non-expert, 3 numbered points)

1. **What has been proven** — {{≤3_SENTENCES}}
   <!-- example: "Battle-tested 8-gate input filter delivers ~85-95% accuracy across 12 dossiers. Adding 8 synthesis protocols on top closes 5 specific gaps (concept tracing, TL;DR, 400w consensus, methodology audit, formal assumption surfacing) that the input filter alone cannot address." -->

2. **What is still unknown** — {{≤3_SENTENCES}}
   <!-- example: "Whether all 8 synthesis protocols add net value across peer orchestrators in different domains, or whether 2-3 prove redundant outside the original context. Forward-apply on the next orchestrator is the experiment." -->

3. **Why it matters** — {{≤3_SENTENCES}}
   <!-- example: "Research mis-allocation is the most expensive error class in the project (6-figure equivalent at stake across reserves + opportunity cost). 30-40% improvement in synthesis quality compounds over every future locked decision." -->

#### Master Synthesis (Protocol 6 — ≤400 words, 4 sections)

**Established Consensus (~100w)** — {{CLAIMS_CROSS_DOSSIER_ANALYSIS_CONFIRMED}}
<!-- example: "Project operates 3 peer orchestrators with 12+ shipped dossiers and 9 locked entries. The 8-gate per-dossier input filter (Source / Version / Stack / Cost / Implementation / Cross-reference / Existing-knowledge / Quote-extraction) has battle-tested accuracy. Severity tagging, numeric confidence, verbatim quote extraction, freshness gates, stack-fit overrides, TCO discipline, re-verification cadences, cross-DECISIONS reconciliation are project-wide disciplines that work." -->

**Active Debates (~100w)** — {{WHERE_EVIDENCE_IS_SPLIT_OR_EVOLVING}}
<!-- example: "Two synthesis stances coexist — post-hoc analytical (the cross-dossier protocols) vs forward decision-construction (the ranked-roadmap pattern). Earlier framings positioned them as competitors; correct framing treats them as different epistemic layers. Whether to adopt third-party protocols verbatim or wrapped with project discipline overrides remains the central question." -->

**Strongest Evidence (~100w)** — {{TWO_TO_THREE_VERBATIM_QUOTES_OR_STUDIES}}
<!-- example: "Our tiered tension-resolution table is richer than the 5-column Contradiction Finder it could be replaced with — proving framework depth on at least one dimension. Reversal triggers per stage + re-verification schedule + cross-DECISIONS reconciliation are forward-decision disciplines absent from any third-party synthesis protocol. The 12 shipped dossiers passed 8-gate verification with zero rework — direct evidence Layer 1 works at scale." -->

**Key Open Question (~80w)** — {{SINGLE_QUESTION_THAT_WOULD_MOST_CHANGE_THE_RECOMMENDATION}}
<!-- example: "Will the 5 newly adopted protocols deliver the projected ~30-40% synthesis quality uplift in a different orchestrator domain, or will 2-3 prove redundant outside the original context? The next orchestrator dispatch is the experiment; signal at first deliverable." -->

#### Full Decision Body

**Decision** — {{CHOSEN_PATH_WITH_LAYER_BOUNDARIES}}
<!-- example: "Adopt 3-layer research methodology architecture. Layer 1 = unchanged 8-gate framework (battle-tested). Layer 2 = NEW 8 cross-dossier analytical protocols (inherits 14 Layer 1 disciplines). Layer 3 = unchanged forward construction, selectively enhanced with 5 new prefix sections. DECISIONS template extension: every new entry starts with TL;DR + Master Synthesis 400w before dense lock body." -->

**Forward-only** — {{WHAT_REMAINS_CANONICAL_BASELINE}}
<!-- example: "Closed corpora (12 prior dossiers + framework synthesis + earlier locked entries) are canonical baseline. Layer 2 applies starting next orchestrator onwards. No retroactive supplement, no rewrite of any prior artifact." -->

**Rationale** — {{AUDIT_FINDINGS_AND_HOW_THIS_RESOLVES_THEM}}
<!-- example: "Audit of incoming protocols found ~60% blended new value (some 100% new, some 30% overlap). Naive bolt-on would have created 10 anti-patterns (W1-W10) — pejorative methodology framing, fixed assumption counts, padding when no concept lineage exists. Deep analysis surfaced 14 strengths in the existing framework that must be preserved. Optimal architecture: 3 distinct layers, neither replacing the other." -->

**Critical issues uncovered** (independent of the central question; fixed by this lock):
- {{ISSUE_1}} — {{FIX_1}}
- {{ISSUE_2}} — {{FIX_2}}
<!-- example: "🚨 Cursor mirror was MISSING (rule-sync violation). Created. 🟡 8-gate methodology lived in skill, not rule — every session reasoned from different mental model. Fixed: rule extended with §Methodology pointing to all 3 layers." -->

**Files created / modified** — {{ARTIFACT_INVENTORY}}
<!-- example: "Created: `docs/reference/synthesis-protocols.md`, `.cursor/rules/research.mdc`, `.claude/skills/research-synthesizer/SKILL.md`. Modified: `.claude/rules/research.md` (+§Methodology), `docs/prompts/NEXT_ORCHESTRATOR.md` (synthesis section mandates 3-layer structure)." -->

#### Reversal triggers

Per stage of the staged roadmap, what would unwind the lock. Each trigger: decidable from observable facts + severity-ranked + points to a specific alternative path.

- **Stage 1 ({{TRIGGER_CONDITION}})** — {{IF_OBSERVABLE_FACT_X_FIRES}} → {{ALTERNATIVE_PATH_Y}}
  <!-- example: "Forward-apply experiment: if 2+ Layer 2 protocols add zero net value in the new orchestrator domain (judged by reviewer subagent on first dispatch) → drop those protocols from the canonical doc + skill for future deliverables." -->
- **Stage 2 ({{TRIGGER_CONDITION}})** — {{IF_OBSERVABLE_FACT_X_FIRES}} → {{ALTERNATIVE_PATH_Y}}
  <!-- example: "Cross-orchestrator scaling: if protocols feel forced on a third+ orchestrator (different domain character), revisit and prune." -->

